  Name: F-14 Tomcat
  Information: The Grumman F-14 Tomcat is a supersonic, twin-engine, variable-sweep
    wing fighter that served as the U.S. Navy's primary air superiority fighter and
    fleet defense interceptor from 1974 to 2006. Designed for carrier operations,
    it is famous for its long-range AIM-54 Phoenix missile capability, high speed
    (Mach 2.34+), and, later, its "Bombcat" air-to-ground precision strike role.
  Manufacturer: Grumman Aerospace Corporation
